    "breadcrumb": "Curriculum Structure \u003e Spiral Threads",
    "content": "Thread: Git \u0026 Version Control Working draft for faculty review. A spiral deepens through escalating passes across blocks. This is the spiral; one of nine spirals (alongside three lenses and one bounded practice).\nIn one line: Read history → commit/revert safety net → solo branching → collaborative workflow.\nCharacter Redesigned from a single late pass into four. Version control as ’tracking how things change over time’ is introduced as a READING tool first, before it is a workflow tool.\nPasses across the two years Block Host context What’s new at this pass B1 (Y1 Fall) CS-101/102 (embedded) Git as a history-reading tool: log, diff, blame; semantic versioning as “what a version communicates.” Not yet a workflow. B2 (Y1 Fall) CS-105 Code Reading \u0026 Repair Commit and revert as a safety net for repair work. B5 (Y2 Fall) CS-202 (embedded) Solo feature branching — try a schema alternative safely; branching as a solo skill before a team skill. B6 (Y2 Fall) CS-205 Collaborative Development Collaborative Git: PRs, code review, merge conflicts with other people’s changes. Connections Semantic versioning (B1) returns at B8 as an API compatibility contract (Boundaries thread) — closing a two-year loop. Open questions for faculty review None outstanding. For how this lands in a specific block, see that block’s review file.",
    "description": "Thread: Git \u0026 Version Control Working draft for faculty review. A spiral deepens through escalating passes across blocks. This is the spiral; one of nine spirals (alongside three lenses and one bounded practice).\nIn one line: Read history → commit/revert safety net → solo branching → collaborative workflow.\nCharacter Redesigned from a single late pass into four. Version control as ’tracking how things change over time’ is introduced as a READING tool first, before it is a workflow tool.",
    "tags": [],
    "title": "Git \u0026 Version Control",
    "uri": "/two-year-refactor/03-curriculum/threads/git/index.html"
