    "content": "Working draft for faculty review. A spiral deepens through escalating passes across blocks. This is the spiral; one of nine spirals (alongside three lenses and one bounded practice).\nIn one line: Systems and the humans who build them are one structural fabric — from observing the parallel, to living it, to reflecting on it.\nCharacter Models the BUILDERS structurally, not just the users — extending the notional machine’s top layer. Seeded conceptually, then lived through the team project, then reflected on. Complements the Git collaboration thread (Git is the tool; this is the social reality the tool serves).\nPasses across the two years Block Host context What’s new at this pass B4 (Y1 Spring) CS-111 Systems \u0026 APIs SEEDED: Conway’s Law — systems mirror the organizations that build them. Conceptual; links system structure to human structure. B6 (Y2 Fall) CS-205 Collaborative Development ENACTED: the team IS an organization now. Communication overhead, Brooks’s Law. How they divide work shapes what they build. B7 (Y2 Spring) CS-206/207 Design Review DEFEND/RETROSPECT: defend not just technical structure but how the team organized to produce it. B8 (Y2 Spring) CS-209 / System Integration Project REFLECT: blameless postmortem — the org-culture expression of “errors are normative.” Connections B8 blameless postmortem converges with the Computational Models/Error Handling thread (errors normative). Complements the Git thread’s collaborative passes. Open questions for faculty review Confirm human/organizational structure belongs in the technical foundation (it was a deliberate inclusion from the ‘structure across scales’ frame, naming ’even the humans’). For how this lands in a specific block, see that block’s review file.",
